(Maternal-Newborn Safety: Magnesium Sulfate) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Magnesium Sulfate is a central nervous system depressant used to prevent seizures in preeclampsia and eclampsia. It is also used as a tocolytic to stop preterm labor.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Therapeutic Level:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(The therapeutic range is 4.0 to 7.0 mEq/L.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Monitoring for Toxicity:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(Nurses must assess the client closely for signs of magnesium toxicity:) Tj
0 -15 Td
(1. Absent deep tendon reflexes \(DTRs\) is usually the first sign of toxicity.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(2. Respiratory rate less than 12 breaths per minute.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(3. Urinary output less than 30 mL/hour, which leads to magnesium accumulation.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(4. Severe hypotension or cardiac arrest.) Tj
0 -15 Td
(If toxicity is suspected, stop the infusion immediately and administer the antidote, Calcium Gluconate \(10% solution, IV push\).) Tj
0 -15 Td
ET
endstream
